Description: It feels heavy in the hand, but once it starts cutting, it's hard to stop.

Name: Smashburgh
Description: You're not sure, but you think this hammer may have been used on a steak.

Name: Stop Poking Me!
Description: This spear has a long reach. Too long, and bothersome.

Name: Mountaineer
Description: The essence of this gauntlet was recovered from an incredibly high peak.

Name: Shimmermist
Description: Sometimes, you're not sure if you can see this gauntlet.

Name: Fwoosh
Description: "That's the sound it makes."

Name: Living Mind
Description: Healing in this world is a connection between mind and body. It requires a living mind to have a living body.

Name: Wrath of Decimus
Description: An act of violence forged into a weapon.

Name: Hoplites Great Blade
Description: The Greatsword of the greatest Legionnaires.

Name: Sagittar of Lucanus
Description: By the pull of its string, violence.

Name: Vesuvius
Description: Its molten core is primed for devastation.

Name: Cuirass of Decimus
Description: Mysterious dark metal forms this chest armor.

Name: Fists of Decimus
Description: These gauntlets bear the strength of a mythical beast.

Name: Galea of Lucanus
Description: Medium helm of a great giant.

Name: Hobnailed Boots of Lucanus
Description: Boots built to survive the rigors of the great cyclops.

Name: Braccae of Lucanus
Description: A pair of trousers to bring the entire set of Lucanus' armor together.

Name: Oasis of Life
Description: A small patch of life in the barren wasteland of battle.

Name: Heatstroke
Description: Remember to stay hydrated.

Name: Stalker's Sand
Description: God damn the sun.

Name: Dunewinds
Description: Desert winds kick up a fierce dust storm.

Name: Sun Seal
Description: Let the sun empower you.

Name: Bloodwalker
Description: Walk the great dunes of blood.

Name: Orichalcum Round Shield
Description: A Round Shield made of Orichalcum.

Name: Orichalcum Kite Shield
Description: A Kite Shield made of Orichalcum.

Name: Orichalcum Tower Shield
Description: A Tower Shield made of Orichalcum.

Name: Orichalcum Crafted Amulet
Description: An orichalcum amulet with an empty socket.

Name: Orichalcum Crafted Ring
Description: An orichalcum ring with an empty socket.

Name: Orichalcum Crafted Earring
Description: An orichalcum earring with an empty socket.

Name: Orichalcum Plate Helm
Description: Plate armor. On the heavier side, but offers good overall protection.

Name: Orichalcum Plate Breastplate
Description: Plate armor. On the heavier side, but offers good overall protection.

Name: Orichalcum Plate Gauntlets
Description: Plate armor. On the heavier side, but offers good overall protection.

Name: Orichalcum Plate Greaves
Description: Plate armor. On the heavier side, but offers good overall protection.

Name: Orichalcum Plate Boots
Description: Plate armor. On the heavier side, but offers good overall protection.

Name: Infused Leather Hat
Description: Leather armor. Offers a good balance of mobility and protection.

Name: Infused Leather Coat
Description: Leather armor. Offers a good balance of mobility and protection.

Description: Leather armor. Offers a good balance of mobility and protection.

Name: Infused Leather Pants
Description: Leather armor. Offers a good balance of mobility and protection.

Name: Infused Leather Boots
Description: Leather armor. Offers a good balance of mobility and protection.

Name: Infused Silk Hat
Description: Cloth armor. Excellent mobility, but affords little protection.

Name: Infused Silk Shirt
Description: Cloth armor. Excellent mobility, but affords little protection.

Name: Infused Silk Gloves
Description: Cloth armor. Excellent mobility, but affords little protection.

Name: Infused Silk Pants
Description: Cloth armor. Excellent mobility, but affords little protection.

Name: Infused Silk Shoes
Description: Cloth armor. Excellent mobility, but affords little protection.

Name: Orichalcum Longsword
Description: 1-Handed. A Longsword made of Orichalcum. Favors Strength for dealing damage, but Dexterity also contributes.

Name: Orichalcum Hatchet
Description: 1-Handed. A Hatchet made of Orichalcum. Favors Strength for dealing damage, but Dexterity also contributes. Can be thrown.

Name: Orichalcum War Hammer
Description: 2-Handed. A War Hammer made of Orichalcum. Exclusively favors Strength for dealing damage.

Name: Orichalcum Great Axe
Description: 2-Handed. A Great Axe made of Orichalcum. Exclusively favors Strength for dealing damage.

Name: Ironwood Bow
Description: 2-Handed. A Bow made of Ironwood. Exclusively favors Dexterity for dealing damage. Fires Arrows.

Name: Orichalcum Musket
Description: 2-Handed. A Musket made of Orichalcum. Favors Dexterity and Intelligence for dealing damage. Fires Cartridges.

Name: Orichalcum Fire Staff
Description: 2-Handed. An orichalcum staff that is used to channel Fire Magic.

Name: Orichalcum Life Staff
Description: 2-handed. An orichalcum staff that is used to channel Life Magic.

Name: Ironwood Spear
Description: 2-Handed. A Spear with an Ironwood haft. Favors Dexterity for dealing damage, but Strength also contributes. Can be thrown.

Name: Orichalcum Rapier
Description: 1-Handed. A Rapier made of Orichalcum. Favors Dexterity and Intelligence for dealing damage.

Name: Orichalcum Ice Gauntlet
Description: A magical gauntlet that channels the Ice element.

Name: Orichalcum Void Gauntlet
Description: Dark energies purr like a kitten in this one.

Name: Orichalcum Blunderbuss
Description: 2-Handed. A Blunderbuss made of Orichalcum. Favors Strength for dealing damage. Fires Slugs.

Name: Orichalcum Greatsword
Description: 2-Handed. A Greatsword made of Orichalcum. Favors Strength and Dexterity for dealing damage.

Name: Orichalcum Flail
Description: 1-Handed. A Flail made of Orichalcum. Favors Strength for dealing damage, and Focus for support.

Name: Unyielding
Description: A helm that defies defeat, offering resolute protection and instilling unwavering determination in its wearer.

Name: Void Darkplate
Description: Clad in the Void Darkplate, become an embodiment of impenetrable darkness, striking fear into the hearts of those who oppose you.

Name: Magnetic Gauntlets
Description: Harness the power of attraction with these gauntlets, manipulating metal and drawing your weapon to your enemies weak points.

Name: Freedom
Description: These pants grant a sense of unparalleled mobility and liberation when worn.

Name: The Unmoved
Description: Root yourself, standing firm against all challenges while maintaining unshakable stability.

Name: Djinn Headwrap
Description: Envelop your senses in the mystique of the Djinn Headwrap, channeling elusive energies and weaving spells with an air of enchantment.

Name: Nimble Coat
Description: Don the Nimble Coat and embrace agility without compromising protection, embodying swift and calculated movements.

Name: Ghoul Gloves
Description: Slip on these gloves, attaining an eerie dexterity that allows you to maneuver through shadows with an eerie touch.

Name: Attuned Leather Pants
Description: Wear the Attuned Leather pants to harmonize grace with protection, ensuring fluidity in combat and evasion when necessary.

Name: Winged Leather Shoes
Description: Step into Winged Leather Shoes, embracing fleet-footed grace and soaring agility as if taking flight on the battlefield.

Name: Grey Wizard's Hat
Description: Crown yourself with the Grey Wizard's Hat to wield mystical prowess, channeling spells with the wisdom and power of a master sorcerer.

Name: Featherweight
Description: Draped in the Featherweight, move like a whisper and strike with unexpected force, catching enemies off guard.

Name: Quickdraw Gloves
Description: Slip on the Quickdraw Gloves to enhance your reflexes, enabling rapid weapon draws and lightning-fast reactions in the heat of battle.

Name: Koya's Knee Guards
Description: These pants have reinforced knee guards and a swirl of energy around them making you harder to hit.

Name: Tumbler Feetwraps
Description: Step into the Tumbler Feetwraps to maintain balance even in the midst of chaos, recovering swiftly from falls and evading with acrobatic finesse.

Name: The Butcher
Description: A blade honed for relentless carnage, cleaving through foes with brutal precision.

Name: Freya's Francisca
Description: Infused with the essence of the Norse goddess, this hatchet delivers swift strikes that echo the wrath of the divine.

Name: Spark of Mjölnir
Description: This hammer channels the lightning of legends, its thunderous strikes electrifying the battlefield.

Name: The Abyss
Description: A Great Axe that hungers for destruction, its immense weight cutting through enemies as if plunging into the depths of darkness.

Name: Boltcaster
Description: Unleash bolts of precision and power with this bow, turning the tide of battle with each meticulously aimed shot.

Name: The Mechanic
Description: A musket engineered to perfection, firing with mechanical precision and devastating impact.

Name: Gladiator
Description: A shield that embodies the spirit of a fearless warrior, deflecting attacks with grace and tenacity.

Name: Michael
Description: A shield swirling with energy, offering protection with swift and righteous defense.

Name: The Wall
Description: A tower shield of unwavering strength, providing an impenetrable barrier for allies behind its unyielding defense.

Name: Inferno
Description: Harness the fury of flames with this staff, conjuring infernos that engulf adversaries in roaring conflagration.

Name: Vengeance
Description: A staff that heals and avenges, turning the life force of allies into a force to be reckoned with.

Name: Scorpion's Sting
Description: This deadly spear has the words "get over here" etched on the handle.

Name: Finisher
Description: A rapier designed for calculated finesse, delivering the final, elegant thrust to conclude any duel.

Name: Deep Freeze
Description: Embrace the chill of this gauntlet, freezing enemies in their tracks and turning the battlefield into a frozen wasteland.

Name: Lifetaker
Description: This gauntlet taps into the void, siphoning the essence of foes to empower its wielder with each strike.

Name: Pestilence
Description: This blunderbuss spreads chaos and affliction, its shot scattering like a contagion among those unfortunate enough to be targeted.

Name: Serenity
Description: A massive greatsword that brings a sense of calm amidst chaos, sweeping through battle with a serene yet devastating force.

Name: Odo
Description: Swing this flail with unpredictable fervor, echoing the chaotic dance of battle in every wild strike.

Name: Endless Thirst
Description: An earring that whispers of insatiable desires, granting heightened strength with each fallen adversary.

Name: Blooddrinker
Description: A ring that pulses with a vampiric hunger, siphoning vitality from foes to empower its bearer.

Name: Lost Stopwatch
Description: A relic frozen in time, its hands forever halted, a token of moments now lost to the ages.

Name: Ankh
Description: Worn as a symbol of eternal life, this amulet radiates resilience and protection to those who wear it.

Name: Survivor's Coat
Description: Bulky plate that protects you from all who would do you harm.

Name: Gilli's Gravity Gauntlets
Description: These gauntlets can hold a kinetic charge that can be unleashed dealing a massive attack. They feel cold to the touch and warmup as they charge.

Name: Ironheart
Description: Forged in intense crucibles, offer unparalleled defense with interlocking iron plates. Gleaming like polished steel, they symbolize durability and empower wearers with an iron heart to overcome challenges on the battlefield.

Name: Nature's Wrath
Description: This coat is a stylish yet rugged garment adorned with intricate nature-themed patterns. Imbued with the essence of the wilderness, this coat offers both protection and a connection to the primal forces of the natural world.

Name: Ghostly Touch
Description: Your empower? My empower.

Name: Azoth Conductors
Description: Raw energy flows through the leggings, each step you take causing azoth to surge within your being.

Name: Cowl of Power
Description: You look extra powerful with this on. Everyone probably fears you. Probably.

Name: Creed Boots
Description: A lightweight and versatile footwear that embodies the principles of discipline and dedication. Designed for swift and silent movement, these boots provide the wearer with the agility needed to follow any creed or path.

Name: Old Crown
Description: Look at all those glittery gemstones.

Name: Vampire's Vestments
Description: Despair has its own calms.

Name: Lich Gloves
Description: There is only darkness.

Name: Runic Greaves
Description: Your foes will cower at how fast you are lumbering at them.

Name: Sin
Description: This hatchet is a wickedly sharp instrument with a malevolent aura. Its finely honed edge is capable of cutting through the toughest materials effortlessly, making it a fearsome tool in the hands of those who embrace the shadows.

Name: Trsna
Description: A demon appears trapped within the hammer, doing all that it can to escape.

Name: Tempest Fury
Description: A force of nature personified. With a massive, swirling blade that mimics the destructive power of a storm, this formidable weapon strikes fear into the hearts of adversaries as it cleaves through the battlefield.

Name: Aconite
Description: Bane of the Basilisk, this bow's poison can kill even the strongest of foes.

Name: Shrapnel
Description: The explosive shells of this musket cause your foes to bleed. Death by a thousand cuts, right?

Name: Burnanator
Description: Chosen weapon of the pyromancers of old.

Name: Heceta
Description: Shines brighter than the sun, giving new strength to your light based spells.

Name: Venom
Description: A deadly weapon designed to deliver swift and precise strikes. Coated with a potent poison that lingers on its razor-sharp tip, this spear ensures that its victims face not only the immediate impact but also a lingering threat.

Name: Dorgort's Blade
Description: A soft fiery glow emanates from the blade, though it is cool to the touch.

Name: Otzi
Description: Take refuge from the cold within my grasp.

Name: Fracture
Description: The very fabric of the metal is held together by a power you do not understand.

Name: Grace
Description: A well balanced blade, as light as a rapier. Holding the blade feels effortless.

Name: Power Stone
Description: The flail leeches the power from your foes, making its bearer stronger in the process.

Name: Chaos
Description: Chaos' chaoticness is only rivaled by the chaos the wielder brings to any situation.

Name: Wit
Description: Insert snarky comment here.

Name: Relentless
Description: *Slaps shield* "You can fit so many friends in this thing."

Name: Justice
Description: Do what is right, not what it easy.

Name: Elemental Band
Description: An intericate caving ontop a band, with symbols matching all of the natural elements.

Name: Phoenix
Description: Adorned with fiery insignias, bestows its wearer with the resilience to rise from the ashes of adversity, granting a renewed vigor in the face of challenges.

Name: The Captain's Deal
Description: “A thousand notches on a dead man's blade. Only a thousand more to go.”

Name: Greater Purpose
Description: "Where does mankind come from? You shall find out."

Name: Corpse Bride's Command
Description: "The corpse bride ordered her servants to go forth and carry out her judgement on those she deemed unfaithful."

Name: Mourning Light
Description: “Do not shed tears for me, I shall return by dawn.”

Name: Horror of the Night
Description: "For all the horrors the townsfolk may see during the day, what comes at night is far worse than what they can imagine."

Name: Salvation
Description: "Bend the arcane to your will, and you will find even death eludes you. Whether that is a blessing or a curse, I do not know."

Name: Scorn
Description: "My disdain for them is matched only by my desire to wipe them from this place."

Name: Brevity
Description: "From a distance, it sounds like a bough breaking in the winter snows."

Name: Truth
Description: "Speak. I will listen. I will know."

Name: Siren's Rapier
Description: "The sirens were fine duelists, whether it be with spears of rapiers. Few could stand against them."

Name: Winterbite
Description: "Snow is soft. Ice is violent."

Name: Murky Waters
Description: "Nothing was clear, except that the Void was near."

Name: Blinding Light
Description: Faced with the light, they can only move on.

Name: Soulstep
Description: It draws energy from your future to give strength to you now.

Name: Reconciliation
Description: "We hated each other for a long time. We didn't speak to each other. Until one day, we didn't and we did."

Name: Patience
Description: "Deep breaths. In...out. In...out. In...draw. Out...loose."

Name: Avarice
Description: "Look upon others and want not. Or do. No one can stop you."

Name: Restraint
Description: "Strike with intent. Know when it is time and when it is not."

Name: Spirituality
Description: Many souls have inhabited this flail over the aeons. And when your time comes, you shall be the next.

Name: Verdant Agony
Description: “Edengrove cries out in pain, you must defend her.”

Name: Shatterspike
Description: "Massive thorns line the blade of the hatchet."

Name: Tendril of Thalum
Description: "The blessed tree was sacred for the Dryads, until misguided explorers ripped its limbs from the earth. This hammer is all that remains."

Name: Nature's Truth
Description: "Nature cares not for your morals."

Name: Azoth Imbued Spear
Description: "Brimming with pure azoth infusion, this spear is bursting at the seams with raw energy."

Name: Edengrove's Hope
Description: "Stand with nature and defend her. For she is pure of heart and gives hope to all around her."

Name: Forest Fire
Description: "Let loose the spark that will engulf the forest."

Name: Beast's Demise
Description: "The boar rushed me thinking it would gore me. It had no shot."

Name: Oversized Wood Chopper
Description: "Surely this axe can chop down any tree."

Name: Changeling's Rapier
Description: "What form I take is of no concern to you."

Name: Fractured Bough
Description: "I heard cracks in the distance. At first I thought them to be muskets, but they were trees collapsing under the weight of winter."

Name: Silent Grief
Description: "He stares ahead blankly. His eyes betray his grief."

Name: The Gardener
Description: The residents didn't quite care for the caretaker.

Name: Malevolent Defender of the Sage
Description: "While nature is quite adept at reclaiming things lost to time, it is more efficient to not lose them in the first place."

Name: Elegant Lamplighter
Description: "Light the village and keep the dark things away."

Name: Barkbite
Description: Coed yr hen a mwsogl amser.

Name: Sprigganstrike
Description: "A well placed spear can strike between the warped and tangled wood that spriggans use for armor.

Name: Monstrous Sprigganslayer
Description: “Cut the collossus down and free the wilds.”

Name: Spriggan Slicer
Description: "You cut the vine and it regrows faster and stronger to kill you with."

Name: Branch of Deretole
Description: Crafted from the fallen iron branch of a giant tree. Or at least, what the scavenger assumed to be a tree.

Name: Branchbreaker
Description: The keepers of the forest can't always let it grow unchecked.

Name: Cunning Heartrune of Stoneform
Description:
Harden yourself with layers of stone, cleansing all crowd control debuffs and granting immunity to both stagger and crowd control debuffs for ${5}s.
Heartrunes under GS700 can be upgraded at a Stonecutting station.

Harden yourself with layers of stone, cleansing all crowd control debuffs and granting immunity to both stagger and crowd control debuffs for ${5}s.

Description: Despite its wear and tear, dark energies still flow within it.

Name: Greatsword
Description: Its well-kept edge will make this a reliable partner for years to come.

Description: A deadly swinging weapon.

Name: Firing Line of the Ranger

Name: Hunter's Claw
Description: An unrelenting bow for a hunter with stupendous reach.

Name: Riposte
Description: "Pitiful. Let your sword do the talking!"

Name: Olympian
Description: The body of a god, the willpower of a demon, the luck of a damned soul.

Name: Dark Scream of the Sage
Description: There is power in the Abyss. Power, and Fear.

Name: Agamemnon
Description: "A noble house, tarnished by a treacherous legacy."

Name: Vine of the Barbarian
Description: A grasping tendril, an invasive feeler, ending in a poison barb.

Name: Blaze
Description: Fields of fire, as far as the eye can see. Only blood will pay for this.

Name: Thorn
Description: The cut is not deep, but you will never reach for the brambles again.

Name: Snowdrift
Description: "We will bury you."

Name: Spirit
Description: "Creatures of the Earth, take leave upon the Wind, Fire upon mine enemies!"

Name: Spinning Wheel
Description: Blood of our mothers, Sweat of our labor, Tears of our widowers.

Name: You're a Beast
Description: "Necessity and scarcity are The Mothers of Invention." - Inscription on the Underside

Name: The Ring
Description: Lock them in and duke it out.

Name: Immolation
Description: A bright pyre can be a very distracting thing.

Name: Bruiser's Axe
Description: An axe of no particular report. It's most noteworthy feature is how many people have wielded it.

Name: Hero of the Hills
Description: A great warrior once wielded this hammer to hold an army off at the pass.

Name: Fist of Kurok
Description: A proud hammer, a weapon wielded by the chieftain of the troupe.

Name: Footfall
Description: "A thundering came down from the mountain, the heavy footfalls of the stampeding horde."

Name: Not a Monkey
Description: "Truk is not a Monkey, he is an APE!"

Name: A Mad House
Description: "Damn you, you hairy freak!"

Name: Razor's Leaf
Description: Beware the sharp edge of the grass. You can lay down in a field and wake up in blood.

Name: Touch of the Icicle
Description: It feels cold. Cold as death.

Name: Incendior
Description: "Wood, some gunpowder, and a lit match. Sounds like a fun afternoon."

Name: Evolutionary Response
Description: "Everything is an arms race. Fists become Spears, Spears become Bows, Bows become Guns."

Name: Toothpick
Description: Seems small, but sturdy. Should be paired with a fine slab of a shield.

Name: Charon
Description: Remember to bring an obol, as a toll for the ferryman.

Name: Gorilla's Strength
Description: The boulder lands, shattering the earth. Too close for comfort.

Name: Mammoth's Revenge
Description: Trembling earth, shrieking bellows, boiling blood.

Name: Wolf at the Door
Description: The shield is only as strong as the will to hold it.

Name: Pot Shot
Description: "It doesn't shoot real straight, but if you're not really looking to hit anything..."

Name: Orchard
Description: Some scholars dig and dig, and then one day the garden blooms with knowledge.

Name: Nathan's Hammer
Description: The finest craftsmen create the most powerful arcana. And then there's Nathan.

Name: Nathan's Hammer
Description: The finest craftsmen create the most powerful arcana. And then there's Nathan.

Name: Dragon's Scale
Description: A hard shield, basically impenetrable.

Description: Foot Protection found in a beastly den.

Name: Fallen Olympian
Description: A relic of another Era. One filled with courage, pride, and rage.

Name: Explorer's Torch
Description: The wilds are daunting at night, let this staff guide your way.

Name: Magistrate's Cloak
Description: The trampled and worn down cloak of the old Magistrate. It must have been lost when First Light was evacuated.

Name: Jewel of the Tower
Description: A beautiful trinket once stowed in secret in Elafry Pyrgo.

Name: Wit's End
Description: When you're out of options, turn to your trusty rapier.

Name: Agar's Least
Description: The first sword chosen can be the most familiar in hand, but is more often the sign of a desperate man.

Name: Right Hand of Frost
Description: A cold wind follows the path of this clenched fist.

Name: Left Hand of Deceit
Description: "Why does this glove only fit on my right hand?"

Name: Roman Discipline
Description: "Keep formation, guard your neighbor, trust your commander."

Name: Curse of the Descending Sun
Description: Blows from the furthest reach strike with the most fury.

Name: The Band of Set
Description: Chaos and sand. All that ever comes is chaos and sand.

Name: Amalgamation
Description: Together. Whole. We are as One.

Name: Primordial Flame
Description: Travel to the Crux of the World, and you will find the Source.

Name: Tidings of Good Fortune
Description: There will always be Light ahead.

Name: Unbearable
Description: "Well, I mean the BEAR can't use it anymore. What else should I call it?"

Name: The Hard Way
Description: There is an easier way to defeat a Gorgon. You did not take that path.

Name: Red Nose of Doom
Description: Fire and Smoke. The Sleigh has been lead to its demise, and from the sulfur and ash comes ruin.

Name: Pillar of Winter
Description: There was only one ship. Inside it, the man with two minds and the captain who would be corrupted. But seasons change, and now the way is frozen.

Name: Worn Upon Stone
Description: The thinner blade fooled the passer-by. They thought it could be removed. Vines strangled the unwary, and so sat the stone, unmoved.

Name: Sharp Eyes
Description: The shots are taken from the grass, the tree, the cliffs. All you need is enough ammunition and sharp eyes.

Name: Legion's Left Hand
Description: An army's legs last as long as its supply chain. An army's heart lasts as long as its homeliness.

Name: Frostclaw
Description: "The swipe of the massive paw nearly took my head as I ducked and drew my bow. Will the arrow find its mark in the belly? Or be deflected by steel-like hide and muscle?"

Name: Tooth and Claw
Description: Nature is a beast. Unruly, untamed. Life will always break free, painfully, even dangerously.

Name: Root
Description: A vine will creep, and settle across vast distances looking for sun, but it will always connect to a base.

Name: Leaf and Stem
Description: The world is not a collection of beasts moving across a dull background. Those plants are survivors, and you would do well to respect them.

Name: Draught of Death
Description: There is power beyond the veil, all you need do is drink.

Name: Weight of the Mighty
Description: "Their footfalls can be heard for miles. Their breath is like a furnace. Their blows like an avalanche."

Name: Frozen Federfechter
Description: Sturdy Rapier, with a tip that burns like Ice.

Name: Moltmasher
Description: War Hammer with the heft and swing of burning stone.

Name: Bolt Barker
Description: "A clap like thunder, a crater filled with glass."

Name: Hunter's Eye
Description: A sturdy bow for a hunter with the vision to change the world.

Name: Pokey
Description: "Yes, I know how a sword works. The pointy end goes into the other men."

Name: Splitter
Description: Trees, Shields, Walls, Skulls. It doesn't matter which.

Name: Gemma's Ear Pebble
Description: Its definitely supposed to be a good luck charm. Not sure if it worked.

Name: Short Stick
Description: "The name is crudely engraved on the pommel. I can only imagine what "Long Stick" might look like."

Name: Missed Buckshot
Description: Putting the "blunder" in Blunderbuss.

Name: Pin-Hole Blower
Description: "You take the powder in, get it nice into the tube, then smack the pin hole! Puts the spark right up the pan, and BOOM!"

Name: Hoof and Tusk
Description: Try to stop the wall of ivory, keratin, and flesh. It will trample you.

Name: Wrecker
Description: Swing Hard, Swing Strong, Have Fun.

Name: Drown Drown Drown
Description: You will drink. You will drown. You will be disposed of.

Name: Our Destiny
Description: We knew it was our destiny to roam free.

Name: Abyss Walker
Description: She walked in the abyss. She held it, gazed into it. No one questioned whether it gazed back.

Name: Bunyan's Axe
Description: "Paul? Yeah, I knew him. No finer woodsman ever walked this land."

Name: Kain's Ring
Description: The ring is an echo of his power. His essense seeps into the very air from it.

Name: Steel Six Draw
Description: Six points, six edges, six attacks.

Name: Whiplash
Description: "Crack went the whip! We could not stop, but for the master's lash."

Name: Brace Under Fall
Description: Dig the haft into the ground, point the spearhead up as the bear falls upon it.

Name: The Dueler
Description: "It's pronounced "Duelist."" "Truly I do not care."

Name: Well of Souls
Description: We all draw life from the same breaths.

Name: Enflamed Chaos
Description: An impossible flame. It seems to burn without a source, all-consuming, and without relent.

Name: Frozen Fire
Description: It is fire, but cold to the touch. It must come from some special hell.

Name: Totemic Power
Description: We put stock in symbols, deities, totems, to give us strength.

Name: The Rat King
Description: A forest of tiny swords, held by a legion of tiny hands.

Name: Black Talons
Description: Her life meant peace in the grove. Her death brought chaos to all.

Name: Eagle's Beak
Description: Sharp keratin can split flesh and crush bone.

Name: Crack
Description: The sound of a whip.

Name: Cantilever
Description: A far reach can be supported by a stable base.

Name: Swipe
Description: The swing of the axe feels like a swipe from massive claws.

Name: Flashpowder
Description: Smoke and ash, nothing more.

Name: Rhinestone
Description: A glittering gem, embedded on the ear of a mighty warrior.

Name: Kernel
Description: Only a seed, but it can grow into a mighty tree.

Name: Heat of the Moment
Description: The most violent acts can be committed in the heat of the moment.

Name: Dragon's Tail
Description: "You thought the dangerous end was the front, didn't you?"

Name: Fury
Description: The untamed fury of the wilderness will drive away all but the bravest souls.

Name: Nemesis
Description: I have many names. Rival. Antagonist. Villain.

Name: Ares' Will
Description: The god of war was a force to be reckoned with.

Name: Thanatos' Will
Description: Death creeps behind. Like a fire, it consumes all, as quickly or as slowly as it desires.

Name: Hades' Fury
Description: Do not cross the King of the Underworld.

Name: Hesperian Gardener
Description: This is a paradise. It needs a minder to keep it that way.

Name: Haphestus' Ingenuity
Description: To honor a clever craftsman and genius tinkerer, I could not think of a better name.

Name: Lockdown
Description: The weight of a hammer so great that none can lift it. Only the strongest can hope to move it.

Name: Reputation
Description: It precedes me, by three feet of steel.

Name: Sundrop
Description: A shiny jewel, set in a bright gold band.

Name: Acorn
Description: These trees were my friends. I had tended to them since they were naught but acorns.

Name: Flower Petal
Description: Its beauty belies ferocity, cunning, and terror.

Name: Blade of the Leaf
Description: In nature, a leaf can cut flesh as well as any blade.

Name: Windbite
Description: The cold wind nips at your foes heels.

Name: Warcry of the Sentry
Description: A gutteral cry seems to fill your lungs while you protect others with this Greatsword.

Name: Voidblast
Description: Something seems to be reaching out from the muzzle...

Name: Calming Rage
Description: This weapons almost seems to be meditating in your hand.

Name: Havoc
Description: A whirl of sharp points and dangerous slashes.

Name: Grovelight
Description: A soft light drew you to find this amulet among all others, like a warm grove in the summer.

Name: Soulpollen
Description: "For trees and bushes to have gained sentience on Aeternum, it should be no stretch to even assert they have a soul."

Name: Genesis of Life
Description: Not exactly primal, but it seems to have such an ancient quality that other words feel almost childlike as a comparison for this small trinket.

Name: Lifewell Channeler
Description: This staff draws its power directly from the deep recesses of the earth where the First Lives began.

Name: Boreal Force
Description: Winter is an indelible part of the cycle of the years just as death is a reflection of our lives.

Name: Hunger of the Void
Description: The quiet void has never once forgotten the time before beginnings and will never let us stray too far from it either.

Name: Ignition
Description: "As dangerous as it may be, even fire is an important part of a healthy forest."

Name: Bramblebranch
Description: Jagged and drought-like to the touch. You wonder if it was meant to harm the victim or the wielder.

Name: Clint
Description: You can barely read a simple name is engraved on the hilt, 'Clint'.

Name: Morgol's Maul
Description: An absolute mountain of a woman. Morgol was feared in many corners of Aeternum for her size rather than her temperament.

Name: Petrified Trunk
Description: "It may not be as sturdy as iron, but such old azoth touched wood must be sturdy enough, no?"

Name: Spiralseed
Description: If shot true, arrows from this bow seem to dance and scream through the air as they chase a target.

Name: Meatgrinder
Description: Fertilizer is a necessity to caretake a forest of this size and, well, something has to make all of it.

Name: Iceburst
Description: "As the land shifts through time, so too do travelers shift through the land. Leaving all their bloody trash too!"

Name: Hollow Trunk
Description: A bolt of lightning from the blue opened a tree and this fell out. Don't ask me how it got there, I don't know either.

Name: Jackalope Antler
Description: Long thought to be an old wives tale, perhaps such cryptic creatures ended up in Aeternum.

Name: Enchanted Root
Description: As wyrdwood grows taller and taller, it must reach further, and further to find azoth in the soil. Not every root finds the nutrients, and must be abandoned by the trees.

Name: Cleansing Whip
Description: A strange tool to any who are not native caretakers of the forest.

Name: Chrysalid Chitin
Description: It seems to be less of a coat, and moreso a… piece of a cocoon…? But what insect could even be large enough to molt shards this large?

Name: Wandering Helm
Description: This hat has seen many heads in its travels. I really wouldn't recommend wearing it though.

Name: Treetop Down
Description: These pants are soft enough that you feel you can remember what it was like to swing in the treetops.

Name: Moss Stompers
Description: Such heavy boots are invaluable while crossing swamps and moors. Though the denizens of such lands won't appreciate your intrusions.

Name: Berry Pickers
Description: Simple but tough leather is invaluable when trying to gather berries from their protective bushels of thorns.

Name: Passage of Time
Description: It's better to go with the flow, than to vainly fight against it.

Name: Hamstring
Description: This seems to be a keepsake from some kind of graverobbing scum.

Name: Heavy Earring
Description: The extremely dense stones in its craftsmanship have allowed mages to infuse a great deal more azoth into this earring than you would expect.

Name: Ritual of the Hereafter
Description: "Just as we must shepherd those through life, we must also ensure they are guided in death."

Name: Gravelguard
Description: While this may be an ice gauntlet, you'd be a fool to assume the only rock it throws is blue.

Name: Ritual Blessing
Description: An invaluable tool for a guiding cleric. It may not serve you as well in combat as it did its previous owner at the altar.

Name: Flamewood
Description: "You stole my firewood to make a staff? I guess you can keep it, but, why not just go cut down a tree…?"

Name: Second Wind
Description: The second wind is where champions and warriors are made. Usually because that's when people end up dead, and you can't be a winner if you lost.

Name: Hewn Stone
Description: Don't let the rough craftsmanship fool you, it's as sharp as it needs to be to stab you.

Name: Cold Heft
Description: The weight of Winter is more than most expect.

Name: Primal Rage
Description: You can feel the fate of the planet in your hands. Fight well.

Name: Snowcoated Shortbow
Description: A frost coated arrow has quite the shock to it when it pierces flesh.

Name: Warhorn
Description: Its blast signals the start of the fight, and the end of a life.

Name: Firing Line
Description: Formation and organization are almost alien concepts to a battlefield such as Aeternum.

Name: Warrior's Shame
Description: "Aim for the back, not only because it’s a bloody large open space, but because it will disrupt your opponent's rhythm and set them on edge."

Name: Stalagmite
Description: A heavy piece of stone that fell off the ceiling of an ancient cave. Or did it come from the ground?

Name: Bouldershard
Description: This blade did not come from a boulder, but due to its size, that's a very reasonable assumption.

Name: Morale
Description: Charge forward into the fray!

Name: Weathered Concrete
Description: Even after centuries of weathering and damage, this helm stands as strong as the Pantheon itself.

Name: Reverent Earth
Description: You feel the slow, muttering prayer of the land while you wear this helmet.

Name: Ancient Anchor
Description: The weight of these leg guards is so great you feel that you can't be moved. Which does pose a problem, as walking tends to be important.

Name: Stonesole
Description: "Gary I hate you so much. Gloves are gloves and shoes are shoes, these aren't even similar."

Name: Stonesoul
Description: "Reg, do you think you could wear these on your feet? Gloves are kinda like shoes but for your hands!"

Name: Cleansing Pod
Description: A small seed pod. It seems the wild growth is spreading further and faster than you could have thought.

Name: Vivify
Description: It seems to have been cleansed and brought into new life. Though what caused such densely corrupted metal to change may be beyond your ken.

Name: Slaked Thirst
Description: The corruption contained within this trinket has been satisfied. For now.

Name: Monk's Prayer
Description: This staff seems to have resisted the opaque corruption surrounding it, perhaps due to the earnest prayers of the monk who used to walk with it.

Name: Frostlife
Description: Another strange magical item for such a densely corrupted deathtrap. Though this one seems to still be in the process of its cleansing. How powerful must this cleansing force be?

Name: Voidrage
Description: The void flows through you to grant you power. As long as you keep it fed, it will keep you strong.

Name: Flame Brawler
Description: A strange choice of weapon, but staves have been a reliable choice for many people defending themselves over the years.

Name: Vicious Slayer
Description: Powerful thrusts to turn your foes to dust.

Name: Razor's Edge
Description: Not a very imposing weapon, but certainly one that will be quite dangerous in skilled hands.

Name: Willpower
Description: A warrior's will of iron cannot simply be shattered.

Name: Voidwell
Description: Spending so much time in the depths of the void will change even the most immutable of materials.

Name: Darksight
Description: As you feel the depths drag you down, your eyes turn further upwards.

Name: Artillerist
Description: It seems to be a fallen relic from a failed expedition.

Name: Discomfort
Description: If you're willing to step into a strange space you may find this musket to be a reliable partner.

Name: Deadly Cyclone
Description: Just be careful not to get dizzy.

Name: Sharpridge
Description: The corruption doesn't seem to have sharpened the blade, though you're certain it's significantly more dangerous.

Name: Heavenly Punishment
Description: It was dropped from the heavens, as if to curse the malignant corruption.

Name: Commanding Stance
Description: An overflowing confidence from the commander as she leads her men on an ill-fated expedition.

Name: Exploratory Desire
Description: A foolish wanderer to have delved into such malignant corruption in the hungering greed for glittering gold.

Name: Cavernous Thoughts
Description: You feel that this helm has expanded your mind, though you've yet to fill it with anything so it feels rather empty for now.

Name: Devilish Stamina
Description: The unflagging stamina of your demonic foes fills your legs.

Name: Enduring Struggle
Description: The resistance against enduring corruption can never cease.

Name: Fallen Monk's Gloves
Description: A poor lost soul left these behind.

Name: Seafaring Blessing
Description: An old prayer to protect sailors is imbued within this insignificant trinket.

Name: Privateer's Heirloom
Description: A certainly stolen token. It's difficult to justify calling it an 'heirloom' if it was taken from a poor soul on the seas.

Name: Plundered Hoop
Description: A fanciful decoration that used to adorn a pirate's ear.

Name: Swabbing Staff
Description: You make do with what you have in a ship on the seas.

Name: Shardshot
Description: Jagged edges and ridged shards fly from its palm. Even the gauntlet itself stabs at you while you wear it.

Name: Bursting Void
Description: A burst of strength pours forth from your hand and surges outwards.

Name: Lighthouse
Description: A warm light guides you home, and comforts your return.

Name: Boarding Harpoon
Description: A dangerous, but invaluable, tool for any scourge of the high seas.

Name: Captain's Rapier
Description: Arguably more ornamental than functional. Though a weapon is a weapon, even on the sea.

Name: Iceberg
Description: Ice usually is not a particularly dangerous rock, but on the sea it becomes for more concerning.

Name: Rogue's Tool
Description: Rogueish individuals may be known for more discreet tools, but really anything will do if their victim's back is turned.

Name: Oil Jar
Description: Small jars of oil seem to be enchanted to this bow, though how they are attaching themselves to the arrows it fires remains a syrupy mystery.

Name: Berserking Slayer
Description: You've never known a berserker to be more interested in firing a tool than bludgeoning their foes, but to each their own.

Name: Thick Powder
Description: A unique powder blend makes this musket a bit heavier before you fire, though you do certainly feel lighter afterwards.

Name: Deepaxe
Description: You aren't sure if this axe was named for a dark cavern or the cold depths of the sea, though its circumstances ceratinly imply the latter.

Name: Pirate's Cutlass
Description: "Gary, this isn't a cutlass, it's a longsword at best. You can't just call something what it's not. Yes Gary I know we're Pirates but we have bloody standards."

Name: Mizzenmast
Description: You could argue this to be any old piece of wood, but the sheer size of it implies it must have come from a mast.

Name: Heavy Chain
Description: The heavy chain makes this flail a bit more unwieldy, but definitely more deadly.

Name: Soggy Hat
Description: You'll certainly regret wearing something so… mildewy…

Name: Sinking Petticoat
Description: A captain always goes down with her ship.

Name: Padded Shoes
Description: While not particularly protective, these shoes make for excellent comfort while trapped on a slab of wood in the open water.

Name: Frosted Tips
Description: The gloves make you feel extremely cool.

Name: Thin Britches
Description: While they certainly won't keep the cold out, they also aren't keeping the heat in.

Name: Azoth Battery
Description: The amount of azoth stored in here would astound any scholar.

Name: Fiery Force
Description: A burning heat will leave a mark on your finger if you wear this for too long.

Name: Lifeloop
Description: Life begets energy and energy begets life.

Name: Soft Warmth
Description: The comforting warmth of a soft bed protects you.

Name: Frozen Soul
Description: You can't tell if this gauntlet houses a miserable trapped soul, or is just, really, REALLY cold.

Name: Hatred of the Void
Description: As the void surges forth so too does its hatred at anything within the light.

Name: Hungering Flame
Description: The flames lick at their victim, as if to consume everything about them, down to the last ash.

Name: Spear of the Defender
Description: A protector is a valiant warrior indeed. For what could be more noble than protecting the weak?

Name: Steeleater
Description: Any tool that can rend metal will most certainly also rend flesh.

Name: Hippopotamidaen Strength
Description: "Gary. That's not. Hippopotamidaen isn't a word, Gary. Latin, and also English, don't work that way. And besides, Hippos aren't even real. You shouldn't believe everything a Bard tells you Gary."

Name: Brawling Axe
Description: A weapon more suited to a tavern brawl than a proper duel.

Name: Thundershot
Description: A bolt from the blue.

Name: Mayhem Maker
Description: This gun is not so suited for killing foes as much as it suited for wanton destruction.

Name: Ammit's Hunger
Description: Not a particularly accurate name, but then again, whomever named it certainly isn't familiar with the proper Pantheon.

Name: Slayer's Axe
Description: Not so much a warrior's weapon as it is an executioner's tool.

Name: Finger of Suetekh
Description: Power and energy course through this sword in a way you simply can't comprehend.

Name: Arm of Horus
Description: The power of the Gods comes down upon your foe.

Name: Timelost Flail
Description: A weapon out of time, and in a land out of sync.

Name: Graverobber's Hat
Description: Those who would steal from dead people and dead lands such as these deserve their grisly fates.

Name: Shieldline
Description: A thick undershirt worn by many Heavy Knights underneath their breastplates.

Name: Coalsole
Description: You feel a burning heat on your feet as you walk while wearing these.

Name: Dry Leather Gloves
Description: Many years in the sun has dried out these gloves, you can almost feel them sucking the moisture out of you.

Name: Hearty Pants
Description: These pants are not very regular. They do however make you feel healthier.

Name: Empty Hearth
Description: Cold and empty. You aren't sure if anyone flame could reignite this.

Name: Red Hot Slag
Description: A piece of waste taken from the Empyrean Forge. Ordinarily, you'd be quite foolish to want this, but the lingering energies of the forge have enchanted some amount of power into this.

Name: Charcoal
Description: A piece of valuable fuel for many fires. You however? I have no idea what you're going to do with it.

Name: Fire of Life
Description: The fire of life burns within you.

Name: Snowmelt
Description: It's surprising that this gauntlet has even lasted in the forge for this long.

Name: Brightdark
Description: Even within the creeping recesses of the void, hope can be found.

Name: Volcanic Staff
Description: Explosive power and heat erupt out of this seemingly benign staff.

Name: Firepoker
Description: A useful tool in the forge to stoke the flames. It will probably serve well enough as a weapon.

Name: Knightslayer
Description: Far more adept at slipping between armored plates than it is at slicing through your foes.

Name: Firefight
Description: "Yes. You are fighting 'with fire'. You are technically 'fire fighting', Gary. You are technically not wrong Gary."

Name: Trickshot
Description: A skillful warrior can put such a weapon to good use.

Name: Old Longbow
Description: The wood composing this bow has charred over the years of exposure.

Name: Shredder
Description: This won't kill your foes as much as it will shred them into piece.

Name: Flamespout
Description: The extra-volatile powder this gun uses makes it spurt flames on shot.

Name: Commanding Strike
Description: A powerful strikes compels the receiver to kneel.

Name: Enduring Will
Description: Stand and fight!

Name: Strikeback
Description: Parry and riposte upon your foes.

Name: Rending Flail
Description: This flail seems to have been rather haphazardly forged, but it's quite good at rending through armor because of that.

Name: Dragonsteel
Description: Dragons may not be real, but that's not enough to stop an enterprising merchant from pumping up his wares to his suckers.

Name: Insulating Helm
Description: The metal this helmet is forged from is unspectacular, but the inner portions make it surprisingly comfortable in the summer.

Name: Darkshroud Leggings
Description: The void slowly drips up your legs as you wear this armor.

Name: Counterbalancing Boots
Description: Heavy armor is difficult to move in, but offers some unique advantages to other equipment.

Name: Scaled Gauntlets
Description: Scaled armor may not be in fashion any longer, but it's no less effective.

Name: Daemon Soul
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the soul of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Finger
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the finger of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Bone
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the bone of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Stomach
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the stomach of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the heart of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the palm of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Forearm
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the forearm of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Tooth
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the tooth of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Spine
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the spine of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Heel
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the heel of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Tendon
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the tendon of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the vein of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the eye of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the tongue of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Thigh
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the thigh of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Tail
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the tail of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Head
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the head of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Breast
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the breast of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Foot
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the feet of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the hands of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Name: Daemon Leg
Description: A raving madman has warned you this was made with the leg of a Demon. There's no way that's true, right?

Description: Not the most subtle of weapons, but the sound of rolling thunder covers up the subsequent firing.

Name: Stormbound Rapier of the Brigand
Description: Clouds gather as armies amass, ready for war.

Name: Stormbound Spear of the Brigand
Description: Blue as the sky lit by azoth lightning.

Name: Stormbound Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: Toss this hatchet directly into the chest of the enemy to send a shock to their system.

Name: Stormbound War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: Smashing this hammer to the ground creates a sound not unlike a clap of thunder.

Name: Stormbound Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Some consider lightning to be a concentrated form of fire. Those under attack with this staff experiencing burning sensations would agree.

Name: Stormbound Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: The shock of life pouring back into your body never gets old on Aeternum.

Name: Stormbound Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: The heavens part and down comes the coldest rain you've ever experienced.

Name: Stormbound Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Fry your enemies, drain their resolve, and let the storm come.

Name: Stormbound Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: Unleash a hailstorm of lead with a thunderous roar.

Name: Stormbound Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: It pulses with a tumultous energy, itching to be released in a destructive fury.

Name: Stormbound Flail of the Barbarian
Description: Lightning crackles between each of the ball's spikes.

Name: Harbinger Bow of the Brigand
Description: A compound bow corrupted by demonic beasts. The bladed edge may not kill your foe, but it will certainly deter them.

Name: Harbinger Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: More likely to get stuck in your foe than cleave through them, but to be honest, that sounds like the worse outcome.

Name: Harbinger Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: The metals have been corrupted over eons into a dangerous form. For both its wielder and its prey.

Name: Harbinger Musket of the Brigand
Description: Kept together for its sole goal of slaying demonic foes.

Name: Harbinger Rapier of the Brigand
Description: Not particularly elegant, but more than dangerous enough for monster slaying.

Name: Harbinger Spear of the Brigand
Description: The serrated edge helps to rend the tough hides of large foes.

Name: Harbinger Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: Not quite equipped for slashing, but sometimes brute strength is all you need.

Name: Harbinger War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: While technically just a rock attached to a stick, I would not want to be on the other end of this stick.

Name: Harbinger Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: The central magical focus ensures your flames reach their intended target.

Name: Harbinger Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: Focii on both ends of the staff help to circulate magic through this staff.

Name: Harbinger Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: The chill of the grave follows this robber's prize. Its previous owner may not be far behind.

Name: Harbinger Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: An amalgamation of corrupted materials on your hand. Void magics find such places to be a comfortable home.

Name: Harbinger Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: The vile curse even follows its shot.

Name: Harbinger Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: It may look untrustworthy as a weapon to stake your life on, and you'd be right.

Name: Harbinger Flail of the Barbarian
Description: You can sense a demonic power within the savage patchwork of metal.

Name: Mossborne Bow of the Brigand
Description: Thick as an oak branch and twice as tough to draw.

Name: Mossborne Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: Roughly edged, and difficult to grasp. Still capable of sundering any fool who treads in lands better left alone.

Name: Mossborne Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: Corruption has overcome the old growth and sprouts like weeds on this sword.

Name: Mossborne Musket of the Brigand
Description: The forest reclaims all that falls at its feet, even human tools.

Name: Mossborne Rapier of the Brigand
Description: No one expected a mushroom to grow in such a way, but for a something neither truly alive nor dead, expectations are meaningless anyway.

Name: Mossborne Spear of the Brigand
Description: This branch was torn from the tree before it could finish blossoming.

Name: Mossborne Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: Rough, but effective. All a berserker needs.

Name: Mossborne War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: Due to the time spent within nature, this weapon has mutated to better suit its natural prison.

Name: Mossborne Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Fire-eating fungus keeps these flames from consuming the whole weald.

Name: Mossborne Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: Not even the mushrooms know where life energies originate from. And if something so old can't answer, perhaps the question should be left to lie.

Name: Mossborne Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Wet and cold is a perfect breeding ground for fungus and fallen foes.

Name: Mossborne Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Torn from a bloated corpse, the fungus has absorbed the energy of decay.

Name: Mossborne Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: It seems to be...alive?

Name: Mossborne Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: You feel connected to the earth beneath your feet as you plant your stance to brace against incoming blows.

Name: Mossborne Flail of the Barbarian
Description: The rough wood seems to have grown naturally into this shape, it appears to be just as strong as any metal.

Name: Bone Wrought Bow of the Brigand
Description: Ancient sinews are nigh impossible to draw, but the added strength is necessary for hunting ancient megafauna.

Name: Bone Wrought Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: Extra weight has been added from the dense bones used to contruct this Ancient's tool.

Name: Bone Wrought Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: A rough edge for a rough time.

Name: Bone Wrought Musket of the Brigand
Description: Archaeologists have given up on explaining this one.

Name: Bone Wrought Rapier of the Brigand
Description: The stab isn't as dangerous as the tears left behind.

Name: Bone Wrought Spear of the Brigand
Description: Taken from the bones of fallen beast, and used to slay its kin.

Name: Bone Wrought Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: This spirit withing this Hatchet will bite down on your target and won't want to let go.

Name: Bone Wrought War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: Face first.

Name: Bone Wrought Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Originally a tool for making fire to cook food, fire has long since been one of humanity's greatest weapons.

Name: Bone Wrought Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: An ancient lifegem adorns this bone wrought healer's tool.

Name: Bone Wrought Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Thick furs adorn this gauntlet to keep the frostbite off its wielder.

Name: Bone Wrought Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Carved in bone and forged in blood.

Name: Bone Wrought Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: The bones of giant beasts were carefully selected to resist the powder in this weapon.

Name: Bone Wrought Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: Such monstrous creatures must be truly terrifying. You thank whatever gods there may be that you do not live in such a world.

Name: Bone Wrought Flail of the Barbarian
Description: Adorned with bones and thirsty for blood.

Name: Befouled Bow of the Brigand
Description: Good luck drawing such a bow; the defiled metals have no intention of bending to mortal desires.

Name: Befouled Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: Vile magics have long since soiled this once benevolent tool. The protrusions grow as corrupts your foes.

Name: Befouled Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: Corrupted to intentionally harbor magics capable of tearing apart a good person's psyche.

Name: Befouled Musket of the Brigand
Description: What was once a tool to protect the weak, has now been corrupted into a vile perversion of its former self.

Name: Befouled Rapier of the Brigand
Description: Originally a lord's ceremonial weapon, it was stolen by corrupted thieves many years ago.

Name: Befouled Spear of the Brigand
Description: Used by many vile fiends to hold down their prey so it can be corrupted for evil benefits.

Name: Befouled Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: A beautiful gem was torn from the head of this once holy tool, leaving naught but a husk in its wake.

Name: Befouled War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: Unlike similar weapons, this war hammer is not so much intended for killing opponents. Its corrupted wielder breaks bones to incapacitate foes.

Name: Befouled Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Long ago, this was a simple torch in a quiet temple. The vile nature of corruption has mutated this into a weapon of war.

Name: Befouled Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: It's a wonder life-giving essence can remain in such a cruel cage.

Name: Befouled Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: A poor soul tried to halt the spreading corruption by freezing their own hand.

Name: Befouled Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Any properly constructed container is a draw for the void.

Name: Befouled Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: Heavy corruption has left this weapon nearly unrecognizable to its original owner.

Name: Befouled Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: The power sloughing off this weapon in tides brings you great... confidence.

Name: Befouled Flail of the Barbarian
Description: A corrupted energy flows within the ball, it almost seems to be alive.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Bow of the Brigand
Description: The Prize was consigned,

Name: Gleaming Pitch Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: And a wrenching pit.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: A glint in the ink.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Musket of the Brigand
Description: And the price had been paid.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Rapier of the Brigand
Description: Who can ever say?

Name: Gleaming Pitch Spear of the Brigand
Description: For down in The Depths,

Name: Gleaming Pitch Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: The avarice of the night grasps them tight.

Name: Gleaming Pitch War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: The fated tale,

Name: Gleaming Pitch Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Perhaps The Prize too heavy,

Name: Gleaming Pitch Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: or perhaps the path was never prepared.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: You may feel their screams.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: But never forget.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: Dead Men Tell No Tales.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: Their cold souls scream for relief.

Name: Gleaming Pitch Flail of the Barbarian
Description: A treasure-like glint flashes from every surface.

Name: The Pharaoh's Bow of the Brigand
Description: Let your arrows soar as high as the mighty eagle.

Name: The Pharaoh's Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: The javelin points of the axe find themselves buried in beasts on the desert.

Name: The Pharaoh's Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: Raise the golden sword high and declare your victory.

Name: The Pharaoh's Musket of the Brigand
Description: The bandages around the barrel treat this musket like the precious dead.

Name: The Pharaoh's Rapier of the Brigand
Description: It took an incredible smith to make such movement in the rapier.

Name: The Pharaoh's Spear of the Brigand
Description: Held by members of an elite guard unit.

Name: The Pharaoh's Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: A life on Aeternum is long and endless. Is there even any need for reverence to the dead in such a land?

Name: The Pharaoh's War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: It was built to crush your enemies in battle, but usually saw more use by squishing wayward beetles finding their way into places they shouldn't be.

Name: The Pharaoh's Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: This one's going to leave some burns.

Name: The Pharaoh's Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: The serpents hold aloft a life-giving gem.

Name: The Pharaoh's Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: As the sun sets on the vast desert the chill creeps its way down your spine.

Name: The Pharaoh's Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Beneath the embalming wraps lies the power of the void.

Name: The Pharaoh's Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: Turning mistakes into all-out gunfights can be deeply effective.

Name: The Pharaoh's Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: Upon the hilt stands a winged figure of power.

Name: The Pharaoh's Flail of the Barbarian
Description: Its beautiful design is best complemented by the splatters of blood it produces.

Name: Pirated Bow of the Brigand
Description: The metal frame gives it extra force, but makes it extra difficult to draw.

Name: Pirated Bow of the Brigand
Description: The metal frame gives it extra force, but makes it extra difficult to draw.

Name: Pirated Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: A ceremonial tool stolen and used for scourging.

Name: Pirated Longsword of the Barbarian
Description: The golden glint in the thief's eye hid the bronze.

Name: Pirated Musket of the Brigand
Description: What began as an old, favorite gun slowly became an ornament after many successful raids.

Name: Pirated Musket of the Brigand
Description: What began as an old, favorite gun slowly became an ornament after many successful raids.

Name: Pirated Rapier of the Brigand
Description: Its apparent fragility may be a lie, but the danger it poses is not.

Name: Pirated Spear of the Brigand
Description: It doubles as the world's most expensive walking stick.

Name: Pirated Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: Used more for blunt work than cutting wallets.

Name: Pirated War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: Two intimidating heads make this a beautiful ceremonial tool.

Name: Pirated Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Taken from an unfortunate wizard who may not have realized thieves were around.

Name: Pirated Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: Taken from an unfortunate wizard who may not have realized thieves were around.

Name: Pirated Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: Stolen for its price, not its use.

Name: Pirated Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: "I'd nicked it hoping to melt it into gold at some point, but it's just so damn cold."

Name: Pirated Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: "I'd nicked it hoping to melt it into gold at some point, but it's just so damn cold."

Name: Pirated Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: The thieves never understood its true use, and now it is relegated to intimidating the crew.

Name: Pirated Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: The thieves never understood its true use, and now it is relegated to intimidating the crew.

Name: Pirated Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: A homemade piece meant to cause mayhem instead of destruction.

Name: Pirated Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: A homemade piece meant to cause mayhem instead of destruction.

Name: Pirated Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: An impractical choice for any sailor, but it sure would look cool on a boat.

Name: Pirated Flail of the Barbarian
Description: "To acquire treasure, you have to break a few skulls."

Name: Molten Bow of the Brigand
Description: You'll have to loose your arrow quickly, you can feel the heat of the bow singeing it.

Name: Molten Great Axe of the Barbarian
Description: It feels a bit lighter than most Great Axes, but the molten blade should be just as dangerous as any axe.

Name: Molten Sword of the Barbarian
Description: The smiths most familiar with something as strange as the Empyrean Forge are well known for their stylish eccentricities.

Name: Molten Musket of the Brigand
Description: "It's such a beautiful piece of workmanship I almost feel bad firing it."

Name: Molten Rapier of the Brigand
Description: The use of molten material makes this rapier quite a bit lighter than those of a more standard make, perfect for highly dexterous wielders.

Name: Molten Spear of the Brigand
Description: The barbed edge makes such a weapon well suited for hunters, though whether they hunt beasts or men may not matter to the weapon...

Name: Molten Hatchet of the Barbarian
Description: The molten heat flowing through the weapon fills you with a fiery fighting spirit.

Name: Molten War Hammer of the Barbarian
Description: The use of heavier alloys in the molten head has preserved the weight of this flaming weapon as opposed to other, similar creations of the Forge.

Name: Molten Fire Staff of the Occultist
Description: While it may not seem particularly attuned to the element of Fire, you can certainly feel the molten power surging within it while you cast.

Name: Molten Life Staff of the Cleric
Description: "Do you... are you sure this is for healing people?"

Name: Molten Ice Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: The smith who made such a carefully balanced creation of fire and ice may not be known to the wielder, but has become a legend through their works.

Name: Molten Void Gauntlet of the Occultist
Description: Hellfire and brimstone don't do such a weapon justice.

Name: Molten Blunderbuss of the Barbarian
Description: The molten material at the mouth of the weapon gives the loaded shot the extra kick as it tears through its target.

Name: Molten Greatsword of the Brigand
Description: The core of this weapon may be standard metal alloy, but the molten edge means even skilled wielders must be careful, lest they accidentally dismember themselves.

Name: Molten Flail of the Barbarian
Description: To effectively wield this weapon, your fury must burn as hot as the molten metal inside.

Description: Due to the time spent within hellfire, this weapon has mutated to better suit its hellish prison.
